'''Cistrome'''
This term http://cistrome.pbwiki.com/ was coined by investigators at the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and Harvard Medical School to define the set of ''cis''-acting targets of a ''tr''ans-acting factor on a gen''ome'' scale. Technologies such as chromatin immunoprecipitation combined with microarrays "ChIP-on-chip" have greatly facilitated the definition of the cistrome of transcription factors and other chromatin associated proteins.